Class CurveTimeSeries<T extends TimePoint>

Type Parameters:
T - 
public class CurveTimeSeries<T extends TimePoint>
extends java.lang.Object

An ordered set of Curve objects with the same TermStructure each associated to a TimePoint. It models both the historical interest rate curves or a scenario of future evolution of curves.

Author:
Luigi Sgro

public double getTimeStep()
Time step of the curve time series. It is the time period between each subsequent curve it is expressed as a fraction of one year
